Governor Proposes Legislation to Increase State Mental Health Facility Transparency

Wednesday,†Bev Perdue announced that she will work with Attorney General Roy Cooper and proposed legislation to increase the transparency of state mental health, developmental disability and substance abuse facilities by making more information in death records public.

