ìIn North Carolina, the welfare of our citizens always comes first,î said Gov. Perdue. ìEnsuring that important information in death records is public will make state facilities more accountable for the people in their care, restore public confidence and rebuild public trust.î

Perdue and Cooperís proposal would require the following information regarding deaths in state facilities to be public information:

- The name, sex, age and date of birth of the deceased;
- The name of the facility providing the report;
- The date, time and location of the death;
- A brief description of the circumstances of death, including the manner of death if known; and
- A list of all entities to whom the event was reported.

